1	2018-03-15 15:54:56.414026+00	1	1	\N	<p>Nacho from Papagayo Bikes will advise on luggage transfer times and give you luggage labels when you meet him at the shop.</p>\n<p>The standard arrangement is that you will be required to make sure your luggage is labelled and ready for pick up by 09.30am each day. Please ask the reception staff at each property where to leave your luggage for the pick-up.</p>\n<p>Luggage will be transferred to your next hotel by 3pm. We do not guarantee luggage transportation if your luggage is not labelled or if it is not ready on time!</p>\n<p>If you intend arriving earlier than your luggage, you may wish to take a change of clothes with you on the bike.</p>\n<p>Please do not put the following items inside the luggage: medicines and lifesaver devices, glass bottles and liquids in general, fragile objects. You should also carry valuables – money/cards and passports with you when you cycle each day. We will not be held responsible for damages caused by non-compliance with these rules.</p>	<p>Breakfast: Included throughout.</p>\n<p>Lunch: Not included</p>\n<p>Dinner. Not included. See restaurant suggestions below:</p>	<p>Please make your way to the Papagayo bike store between 9am & 10am on the first cycling day. Your rental bikes, along with your detailed information pack with route notes, maps and luggage labels will be waiting for you.</p>\n<p>Your contact at Papagayo Bikes is Mr Nacho Campo and he can be reached on telephone number 0034 606 109 765 or 0034 679 955 947.</p>\n<p>Note: Should you wish to go to the store at a different time to the above, it is important that you contact Nacho first and re-arrange a time that suits you all, as the store is not manned all day.</p>\n<p>Papagayo Bikes: There are 2 different bike stores. Your bike rental shop is located within the grounds of Sands Beach hotel. C.Avenida islas Canarias, 18. See map below. Tel: 0034 928 591 418 or 0034 636 130 386</p>\n<p>Your bike rental includes a repair-kit, pump, lock, water bottle and water bottle holder. Helmets are provided but we recommend you bring your own as they will always fit you best. If you require a helmet this must have been advised at the booking stage. It is compulsory to wear a helmet while cycling here.</p>\n<p>At the end of the last cycling day please leave the bikes at the last hotel of the tour, as they will be picked up by 9am the following morning. Please ask the hotel personnel where you should leave the bikes. We remind you that bike rental is not included should you have added pre-or post-trip nights to your trip.</p>
