 is a large pilothouse, an intimate, stylish bar and seating area. The large picture windows offer wonderful views.</p>\n<p>She has an outdoor café and a Jacuzzi on the afterdeck, as well as various sitting areas where you can enjoy meals outdoors. On the sundeck, there is plenty of space and seating including deck chairs.</p>\n<p><strong>Leafde Fan Fryslân</strong></p>\n<p>The imposing, three masted barquentine <em>Leafde Fan Fryslân</em> offers refined accommodation in 12 well-appointed twin cabins (11 m²). The cabins feature two single beds, en-suite shower/wc and a porthole which can be opened to fresh air. Some of the cabins can accommodate a third bunk bed and there is also one single cabin (7 m²).</p>\n<p>The wheel house offers comfortable seating and meals are taken in the restaurant where there is also a well-stocked bar. The sundeck offers plenty of space and seating.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Meals</strong></p>\n<p>On all three vessels, a hearty breakfast is provided each morning along with a packed lunch to take with you on the daily rides. A three-course meal is served each evening.</p>\n<p>Daily complimentary coffee and tea until 4pm.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
